## Diagram Quality Rule (mandatory before posting any diagram)

Any Mermaid diagram uploaded to Slack (or referenced in a Jira comment) MUST
satisfy the **Content Requirements** defined in
`templates/DIAGRAM_TEMPLATES.md` §1
(mirrored at `.cursor/templates/DIAGRAM_TEMPLATES.md` §1).

### Hard gate — do NOT post the diagram unless ALL of the following are true:

- [ ] Uses the standard `%%{init:}%%` dark-theme header from §3.
- [ ] Has ≥ 8 meaningful nodes (excluding the Legend).
- [ ] ≥ 60% of nodes use multi-line `<br/>` labels (title + context/evidence/timestamp).
- [ ] Contains all 5 semantic zones (Context, Symptom, Root Cause, Resolution
      Steps, Verification) — as subgraphs or clearly labeled clusters.
      For non-resolution diagrams (infra, sequence, lifecycle, deployment,
      relationship), map to the closest equivalent zones in the matching
      template in §4.
- [ ] ≥ 1 node cites a real source: `PRODOPS-XXXX`, Confluence page name,
      or Slack channel/thread.
- [ ] ≥ 1 node includes a real timestamp/date from the ticket
      (created, comment date, status change).
- [ ] ≥ 1 node includes a short (≤ 60 char) evidence quote from a log,
      error message, comment, or attachment, wrapped in `<code>…</code>`.
- [ ] ≥ 1 node explicitly labeled as the root cause / trigger.
- [ ] ≥ 1 node shows how success is verified (health check, sync cycle,
      test upload, DAG green, dashboard metric).
- [ ] Every node has an emoji icon from §6.
- [ ] Every node has an inline `style` line with fill + stroke + text color.
- [ ] ≥ 80% of edges are labeled with the action, protocol, or relationship.
- [ ] Ends with a `Legend` subgraph mapping ≥ 3 colors → meanings.
- [ ] No placeholder text remains (`TICKET-KEY`, `Person 1`, `Step 1 —
      concrete action`, `<Summary>`, etc.).
- [ ] No fabricated ticket keys, Confluence URLs, filenames, or commands.
      If a value is unknown → omit the node rather than invent one.
- [ ] Node count ≤ 25 (readability in Slack thumbnails).

### Anti-patterns (any occurrence = do NOT post):

- Nodes labeled `Execute Resolution`, `Do the thing`, `Process`, `Handle
  request`, `Gather info`, or similar vague verbs. Replace with the exact
  command, UI path, file path, or artifact.
- Unlabeled edges in non-trivial flows.
- Missing symptom or root-cause node in a resolution-flow diagram.
- Markdown pipe tables inside a Mermaid node.
- Paragraph-length node labels (> 4 `<br/>` lines).

### On failure of the gate:

1. Regenerate the diagram, adding the missing information from the ticket,
   attachments (`workspace/attachments/{ISSUE_KEY}/`), matched service config
   (`config/ticket-rules/prodops_*.yaml`), and past-ticket search results.
2. If required information cannot be sourced (no attachments, no matching
   past ticket, no Confluence page), reduce the diagram scope rather than
   inventing content. It is acceptable to post a smaller, honest diagram —
   but it must still satisfy the ≥ 8 node / 5 zone / legend requirements
   by pulling more detail from the Jira ticket fields themselves
   (description, comments, changelog, linked issues, reporter/assignee,
   priority, labels, components).
3. If the diagram still cannot meet the bar, post the text analysis
   without a diagram rather than posting a low-quality one.

### Diagram source-of-truth

The **only** valid diagram templates are the 6 templates in
`templates/DIAGRAM_TEMPLATES.md` (mirror: `.cursor/templates/DIAGRAM_TEMPLATES.md`).
Do not invent new template structures. Pick the closest matching template
from §4, copy its skeleton, and fill it with data from the target ticket.
